French team Bordeaux may sell off Samuel Kalu for a discounted fee in the summer transfer window. Kalu and Guinea winger François Kamano for the Bordeaux exit door because of their poor relationship with manager Paulo Sousa, something which clubs will be aware of before making a bid for their services. The Nigeria international has struggled for game time since October 2019, starting only seven of the 20 games played by Bordeaux in the Ligue 1. “When we see the return of François Kamano against Saint-Etienne, he was invisible. Kalu from time to time may hold on to certain matches,” said Sabathier to webgirondins.com. “It will be complicated. The problem is that if you sell both players this summer you are selling them at a discount.